result.execSummary:
The defendant Shafia M. Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery of a Financial Institution [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.87.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes:
To provide DNA Sample and pay surcharge.

Counseling and follow up as recommended by agent.

Defendant shall have no contact with any victims including- Guaranty Bank or Pick-N-Save

Absolute sobriety.  No bars/taverns.  Not to possess alcohol.

No controlled substances w/ out valid prescription.  Not to possess drug paraphernalia.

No gambling and No contact with any casinos.

Defendant shall have no contact with co-defendant, M. Henderson without consent from agent.

To make reasonable efforts to obtain/maintain stable residence.

To make reasonable efforts to obtain/maintain full-time employment.

DOC shall withhold 25% of all inmate monies to pay fines/costs/surcharges/restitution.  The balance due shall be a condition of extended supervision/parole.  If discharged with financial obligations owing, a civil judgment shall be entered and/or other collection procedures will be implemented.

To pay supervision fees as determined by the DOC.
